      "writtenOn": "2017-08-24T22:02:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think that these should be defined in the Host interface and the impls that you have here should be inside of sshHost. One reasons is that this remote side impl is assuming that the other end is a Bourne shell with a user profile and $PATH (to find sha1sum for example)--a very SSH-thing to assume. \n\nIf getLocalSHA1\u0027s feels wrong to put in Host, maybe rename Host to Cxn. We can also decompose local and remote operations into LocalHost and RemoteHost members of a Cxn later if we need that kind of abstraction.\n\nDon\u0027t feel strongly, though, so feel free to pass.",
