    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f9980288_8a42a252",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/common/host/host.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 43,
      "author": {
        "id": 1196209
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-08-24T22:02:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Not that familiar with golang patterns but this was a common problem in Java: folks would sometimes return interfaces and lose some nuance of the class that implements that interface. The guidance there seems reasonable in that it recommends returning concrete types in implementations. It\u0027s also seems to be a restating of the Robustness principle: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robustness_principle .",
      "parentUuid": "48c4a6c8_b548b117",
      "revId": "fb4f7f5913348340bdcd63d50947961a284c0156",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "17c8eb7d_65a6b7e2",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/common/host/host.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 43,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000042
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-08-26T01:38:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i\u0027m getting rid of the interface for now. i\u0027m going to change the thing that\u0027s currently called sshHost to instead be called SSH (not SSHHost because \"Avoid stutter\" in https://blog.golang.org/package-names).",
      "parentUuid": "f9980288_8a42a252",
      "revId": "fb4f7f5913348340bdcd63d50947961a284c0156",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
