    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9b7fbded_6654a267",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/common/host/host.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 101,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000042
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-08-26T01:38:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "hmm. i think that my intent is for the Run and Start functions to guarantee that the commands passed to them will be interpreted by \"a shell\". this seems difficult to avoid, given that the main (and currently, only) implementation of the interface uses ssh. from the spec (rfc 4254, 6.5):\n\n      byte      SSH_MSG_CHANNEL_REQUEST\n      uint32    recipient channel\n      string    \"exec\"\n      boolean   want reply\n      string    command\n\n   This message will request that the server start the execution of the\n   given command.  The \u0027command\u0027 string may contain a path.  Normal\n   precautions MUST be taken to prevent the execution of unauthorized\n   commands.\n\ni suppose that i could make Run and Start take string slices and do the escaping themselves. does that seem better?\n\nmaybe this is all academic at this point since i think i\u0027m convinced that should get rid of the interface, at least until i\u0027m ready to add a second implementation of it.",
      "parentUuid": "ff58f372_1e0ff35e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 101,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 101,
        "endChar": 18
      },
