      "writtenOn": "2017-08-24T00:02:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "my strong preference for the file-copying functions would\u0027ve been to just use rsync and call it a day, but as far as i\u0027m aware, there\u0027s no way to run rsync over an established ssh connection without creating a tunnel or using ControlMaster. i haven\u0027t run into any elaborate syncing scenarios so far: i just need to copy big test binaries to a DUT, copy a tree of test data to a DUT (having smarting syncing may help here), or copy a directory of test output back to the local machine. from my initial testing, tar --gzip is about the same speed as rsync for those use cases.",
      "revId": "fb4f7f5913348340bdcd63d50947961a284c0156",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
