        "id": 1196209
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-08-24T22:02:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This seems fine to me, for now. We can always change it later. In particular, if we ever implement a \"goHost\" concrete implementation of the Host interface, I\u0027d image that that would be a Go static binary on the other end of the connection that does its own crypto and protocol. In that scenario, I think that reaching out to command line tools on the other end of the connection would seem wrong. But, that\u0027s hypothetical at this point. And, to be honest, SSH connections already assume a lot about the remote environment (including running the target user login profile for their login shell).",
